HEADWORD: Leucorrhœa
<hw>Leu`cor*rh⟦oe⟧"a</hw> <pr>(l⟦umac⟧`k⟦ocr⟧r*r⟦emac⟧"⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Leuco-</ets> + Gr. <grk>"rei^n</grk> to
flow.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A discharge of a white, yellowish,
or greenish, viscid mucus, resulting from inflammation or irritation of
the membrane lining the genital organs of the female; the
whites.</def><-- leukorrhea, leukorrhagia -->
